25|$|Benign {{paroxysmal}} {{positional vertigo}} (BPPV) {{is the most}} common vestibular disorder and occurs when loose calcium carbonate debris has broken off of the otoconial membrane and enters a semicircular canal thereby creating the sensation of motion. Patients with BPPV may experience brief periods <b>of</b> <b>vertigo,</b> usually under a minute, which occur with change in position.|$|E
